        "title": "Android - Stop all threads when leaving activity",
        "body": "<p>My app contains an <code>Activity<\/code> which starts a bunch of <code>AsyncTasks<\/code> and recursive functions. Everything works just fine - even when I leave my actitiy via the <code>back<\/code> or <code>home<\/code> button.<\/p>\n\n<p>Is there an easy solution for just stop everything when leaving the activity?<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Edit<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>My background threads make http calls etc. Via my logs I can see that the threads are still running.<\/p>\n",
